{"description": "Why yet another lisp? Why do we need/want a new lisp for the Erlang VM? What is it that makes the existing ones, even Clojure, a bad fit? This talk will give a brief description of the main properties of the Erlang VM and how it affects implementing languages on it. LFE (Lisp Flavoured Erlang) has been designed to run efficiently on the Erlang VM and at the same time be a \"real lisp\" providing Lisp's good bits. We will describe the language and how it uses the properties of the system as well as some of the tooling around it.", "event": {"name": "ClojuTRE 2015", "nickname": "clojutre-2015", "twitter": "clojutre", "url": "http://clojutre.org/2015/"}, "favorite": "0", "file_date": "2016-12-10", "filename": "wherefore-art-thou-lfe-robert-virding", "length": "33:32", "likes": "27", "recorded": "2015-09-11", "short_description": "Why yet another lisp? Why do we need/want a new lisp for the Erlang VM? What is it that makes the existing ones, even Clojure, a", "speaker_twitters": " @rvirding", "speakers": {"robert-virding": {"episodes": [], "hosting": [], "info": {"country": "Stockholm, Sweden", "github": "rvirding", "home": "http://rvirding.blogspot.com/", "name": "Robert Virding", "twitter": "rvirding"}, "videos": [{"event": {"name": "ClojuTRE 2015", "nickname": "clojutre-2015", "twitter": "clojutre", "url": "http://clojutre.org/2015/"}, "filename": "wherefore-art-thou-lfe-robert-virding", "recorded": "2015-09-11", "thumbnail_url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BvCBTpnlqs8/hqdefault.jpg", "title": "Wherefore art thou LFE?"}, {"event": {"name": "Functional Conf 2016", "nickname": "functionalconf-2016", "twitter": "fnConf", "url": "http://functionalconf.com/2016/"}, "filename": "the-erlang-ecosystem-by-robert-virding-at-functional-conf-2016", "recorded": "2016-10-13", "thumbnail_url": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/iypTz5HoE-U/hqdefault.jpg", "title": "The Erlang Ecosystem"}, {"event": {"name": "GOTO Stockholm 2016", "nickname": "gotocon-stockholm-2016", "twitter": "